                </owl:someValuesFrom>
            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">creep rupture time value</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A creep rupture time value is a scalar value specification that specifies the value of the stress rupture time of a loading process which is part of a creep testing process. It quantifies the total duration from the application of load to specimen fracture. It appears as a numeric value with a time unit (e.g., &quot;159.74 h&quot;, &quot;68779 h&quot;), typically found in the creep properties table, results section, or Larson–Miller plots of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the time to rupture of the target creep test piece.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


    <!-- https://w3id.org/pmd/cto/CTO_0000028 -->

    <owl:Class rdf:about="https://w3id.org/pmd/cto/CTO_0000028">
        <owl:equivalentClass>
            <owl:Class>
                <owl:intersectionOf rdf:parseType="Collection">
