        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">creep test piece gamma precipitate fraction value</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition>A creep test piece gamma precipitate fraction value is a scalar value specification that specifies the value of the volume proportion of gamma precipitate which is a member of a microstructure that is part of a creep test piece participating in a creep testing process. It quantifies the relative volumetric abundance of the gamma phase in the material. It appears as a numeric value expressed as a percentage or fraction (e.g., &quot;20 vol%&quot;), typically found in the microstructure characterization or phase analysis section of a scientific paper, and explicitly refers to the gamma precipitate fraction in the target creep test piece.</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


